fiesta

Minix-inspired operating system being developed in parallel with, and with
native support for, https://github.com/gaerisen/riscv. Everything here was
originally written in that repository under the 'osdev' branch, which is now
abandoned. I'm migrating the project to its own repository for a number of very
good reasons:

1. I need a better way to test the RTL for the CPU that doesn't rely on the
assumption that my code constitutes anything resembling full code coverage, so
I'm forcing myself to learn how to write HDL unit tests and do actual good
verification practice.

2. Debugging an OS you're writing on hardware you developed is a NIGHTMARE; you
never know whether each new bug is in SW or RTL, and I never even tried to get
gdb running on the core, nor would I expect anyone else to.

3. Really, the scope of each project is so different that it's a little silly
that they were ever in the same place.

The name 'fiesta' comes from the name 'refactored-fiesta', which is the
automatically generated name that Github gave me when I created this repository.
